                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/15/237301566/87ac671b11a51263e1e810e44048dda0_3092152176998967750.png",
                      "name": "Фу Цзинь",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 5090,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/15/237301566/dd8f5758152aa51a1db8f3f98df320d9_8490048509397913638.png",
                      "name": "Властительница лекарств",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 5084,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/15/237301566/f8b14cc4415930d04b94be9318be76c2_5296540989211877490.png",
                      "name": "Мао",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 5057,
                      "icon_url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/02/02/70239714/d75494fa72798564617469b6393fac97_7912176143644694059.png",
                      "name": "Зверь Сюаньвэнь",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    },
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2076,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/reliquary/Echoes of an Offering/flower_of_life_icon.png",
                      "name": "Echoes of an Offering",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Chenyu's Blessings of Sunken Jade",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Thousands of years later, the Mountain Lord decided to return Chenyu lands to their state before the arrival of people. She believed that she, and the carps, and the snakes all came from nature, so she wanted to return everything to the form that was at their birth. Then the rivers rose and fell with the rains, their paths were not fixed, the tea trees and flowers were not trimmed or cultivated, nor did they exist for humanity. Lingyuan believed that in such an environment, Fujin would regain her true carp form and spiritual strength and frolic in the great rivers. For many years, the Suanni was changing the spirit veins, due to which the soil deteriorated, a thick fog arose, and miasma spread through the vale.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/03/15/237301566/28d436515e5f0695e04a902ebcc79143_827930443524925098.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Fujin, who cares about the people of the vale, asked for the help of the Traveler to restore the spirit veins and change the soil. The Adeptus did not have enough strength to perform the Rainjade Rite herself, so she needed help. She didn't want Qiaoying Village, famous for its tea, to lose its reason for existence. Thanks to Traveler, Paimon and Lingyuan's friend, Little Mao, Fujin was able to gain enough strength to perform a ritual on the sacred mountain and stop Lingyuan. The Suanni accepted defeat and, for the sake of her friend, agreed not to interfere with caring for people.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
